text: Med City FC is a men's soccer club based in Rochester, Minnesota. It competes in the NPSL Midwest Region's North Conference. The club's colors are blue and green. ==History== Med City FC was founded in 2017 by Frank Spaeth, joining NPSL's North Conference as an expansion team. In late 2019, City was announced as a participant in the 2020 U.S. Open Cup due to its performance in the previous season. This would be the team's first appearance in the tournament. However, on March 13, 2020, U.S. Soccer elected to temporarily suspend the tournament due to the ongoing COVID-19 pandemic. ==Current staff== ===Player roster=== Note: Flags indicate national team as defined under FIFA eligibility rules.
